{{Infobox settlement |settlement_type = |subdivision_type = Country |official_name = Amvrosiivka |native_name = Амвросіївка |subdivision_name = Ukraine |image_seal = Amvrosiyivka gerb.png |image_flag = Amvrosiyivka prapor.png |subdivision_type1 = Oblast |subdivision_name1 = [[Donetsk Oblast|Donetsk]] |population_total = 19021 |population_as_of = 2012 |area_total_km2 = 19.4 |established_date = 1869 |established_title = Founded |established_title2 =City status |established_date2 =1938 |elevation_m = |pushpin_map =Ukraine Donetsk Oblast#Ukraine |coordinates = {{coord|47|47|N|38|29|E|region:UA_type:city|display=inline,title}} |blank_name = [[Köppen climate classification|Climate]] |blank_info = [[Humid continental climate#Hot/warm summer subtype|Dfa]] |website = http://www.slavrada.gov.ua/ }} '''Amvrosiivka''' ({{lang-uk|Амвросіївка}}; {{lang-ru|Амвросиевка}}; since 1869) is a city and the [[capital city|administrative center]] of the [[Amvrosiivka Raion]] within [[Donetsk Oblast]] ([[Oblast|province]]), [[Ukraine]]. Its population is approximately {{Ua-pop-est2017|18,413}}.
It was first founded in 1869 as a train station settlement on the [[Kursk-Kharkiv-Azov Railway]], and it received city status in 1938. Since 1896, a cement factory is located within the city, and cement production has been the dominant industry of the city.<ref name="history">[http://ukrssr.ru/Donezkaja.obl/Amvrosievskij.rajon/Amvrosievka.html Амвросиевка entry] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140409002218/http://ukrssr.ru/Donezkaja.obl/Amvrosievskij.rajon/Amvrosievka.html |date=April 9, 2014 }}, in [[The History of Cities and Villages of the Ukrainian SSR]], Donetsk Oblast section pp. 138-48</ref> Also located within the city is a history museum, industrial technical school, 6&nbsp;schools, 11&nbsp;libraries, 9&nbsp;hospitals, a pharmacy, a movie theater, a club, and a sport stadium.
The city's population peaked at about 24,406 in 1979.<Ref name="pop">http://pop-stat.mashke.org/ukraine-cities.htm</ref>
On July 15, 2014, two Ukrainian soldiers were killed and eight wounded when Amvrosiivka was hit by several "Grad" rockets.{{fact|date=October 2014}}
==Demographics== Native language as of the [[Ukrainian Census (2001)|Ukrainian Census of 2001]]:<ref>[http://www.ukrcensus.gov.ua]</ref> *[[Russian language|Russian]] 71.3% *[[Ukrainian language|Ukrainian]] 27.9% *[[Armenian language|Armenian]] 0.3%
